{
  "description": "M2.9.0 cross-language fixture for the signed Loom command canonical envelope (F1). The canonical is canonical_payload(envelope) == json.dumps(envelope, sort_keys=True, separators=(',',':'), ensure_ascii=True) == fabric_protocol::canonicalize. Tests assert that Python and Rust produce identical bytes for each input. The agent-kind case proves the agent canonical is byte-unchanged (additive-only proof: loom fields are command-kind-only).",
  "cases": [
    {
      "name": "command_minimal",
